The Smart Battery System (SBS) is a standardized protocol that facilitates robust communication between rechargeable batteries and electronic devices via the SMBus. It enables the exchange of vital battery information, such as type, model, charge/discharge rates, and temperature, ensuring efficient and safe battery management in a diverse range of products.

In the ANSI standards of battery nomenclature, the C battery is referred to as "14," while in IEC standards, it is designated as "R14," demonstrating the importance of consistent naming conventions in the battery industry to aid consumers in selecting the right battery for their devices.
